<Author>demf
<Content>Lovely setting, great decor, so-so service, awful room, terrible prices I stayed over a weekend, with my wife. We took a package that gave you 3d/2n with dinners and breakfasts for $425, from which you could deduct $75 with a discount offered by the Paradores de Puerto Rico website. Service is corteous (all young), but sometimes a bit intrusive. *Everything* is rationed: from the ice, to the dinner rolls, to the food portions (the food is extremely good, to be fair), to the rooms (ours was tiny; you literally had to squeeze yourself through the front of the bed to reach the extremely noisy A/C and the other side.) In theory, there could be surcharges for everything, from moving a bed, to returning towels outside of a time window... you feel like you're in summons, and not a guest. Then, there are the surprises: you're offered soup as part of a dinner, but they won't tell you they'll charge $6 for each soup bowl, until you get surprised at the end...The ambiance and decor is lovely in the outside (the big pool looks like something out of Town and Country magazine), short of spectacular (they're in the middle of a wildlife preserve, truly blessed when it comes to location), but the rooms leave much to be desired. I found a cockroach in the bathroom, the floor tiles were a bit gritty, and the bed's linens deserved a throught cleaning. Yuck.The prices do not reflect the value offered. One could forgive the small rooms if they were better kept and more hygienic; the food tastes great but if you take the package, you're limited to the same six options all through your stay. The setting is great, but decor and location do not a hotel make... I'm being generous with the rating since everybody there appears to be friendly and receptive to criticism, but it charges 4-star prices for 2-star service. 
