<Author>lynsk
<Content>Not For Everyone Situated in a Nature Preserve on the SW tip of PR, Bahia Salinas is uniquely special for its isolation and location. We spent four nights here in the middle of July. The pool is beautiful. Our room on the second floor was small though pretty. We had no problems with the hot water and the bed was extremely comfortable. We found the staff to be friendly and accomodating.The reasons I write that it's not for everyone are as follows: 1) The resort is on a really narrow strip of property. Since there wasn't much property to care for, I felt that what was there could have been better maintained. 2) The pool, which is beautiful, closes at 7:00 - why? There is nothing else to do here. 3) Since the hotel is in a nature preserve, they are not allowed to spray for mosquitoes, gnats, ect. We ate at the beach side restaurant on our first night and were driven inside by swarms of gnats who ended up swimming in our wine. We were glad we did not opt for the meal plan since we never ate there again. 4) I was sure that breakfast was included in our room rate but was told upon arrival that breakfast was not included. We ate at Mary's bakery every day right down the street. Which brings me to 5) The Rate. We paid about $170 a night - no breakfast incuded. In my opinion - way overpriced.The overall experience of this hotel and surrounding sites was good. There is some good birding to be done on the salt flats. I'm glad we went, but would probably not return to Bahia Salinas Resort. 
