<Content>Don't Judge a Book by its Cover This place was terrible from the inside out! We paid way too much money for what we got. Our room was horrible, beds uncomfortable, we didn't get hot water and even had a lizard in our bathroom and it was not much for a romantic getaway when they put your room in front of the kiddie pool- so at 8am we were woken up to kids screaming. We had brought snorkle gear since they said there would be a place to snorkle, but there was no place to go and the place recommended by the front desk staff was horrible. We couldn't even go in front of the hotel because it was pure muck. They did give us a new room after we found the lizard in our bathroom, but it wasn't much of a difference except we had hot water and no more lizards. We were going to rent a kayak, but there was never anyone there to help us get the boats- you have to call a number off site to gain access to them. It was a good thing my husband and I didn't bring our two small children because there was a mass of bees by the kiddie pool and over 30 dead bees floating in the kiddie pool. We CAN NOT believe the same pictures on the website were actually taken at this hotel. The breakfast wasn't bad, but for 200+ dollars a night it should have been better- everything should have been better. If all you want to do is sit by a pool and read a book and occaisionally look out over the ocean and pay $200/ night- this is the place for you. I feel bad being so critical- but the place was truley terrible and we hope you don't make the same mistake we did by going there- we would not have wriiten this review if they charged $60/night and were honest with their website and what they had to offer. The staff was nice for the most part, but we will NOT be returning or encouraging anyone to go there. 
