<Content>Misleading!!!! This hotel's website was completely misleading!!! First of all...the hotel is far from everything!!!! It is located near a salt marsh and a mangrove (which by the way was in fact beautiful). We paid $179 a night. We were given the very last room in the resort (all the way in the back). The website photos lead you to believe the hotel is on the beach...which it is. However, you cannot use this beach because it is a mangrove. If you want the closest beach it is about 10 minutes away on a number of unmarked roads and very secluded. There is no one on that beach except for youngsters who go there to party. The quality of the room was extremely poor. Not worth the money at all. No telephones, old comforters on the bed, smelled funny, cheap tv, not enough channels, no iron, NOTHING!!!! When I called (from my cell) to request an iron, I was told I would have to walk all the way to the lobby to pick up an iron and table. Ridiculous! I would not return to this hotel. I stayed at Rosa del Mar in Hatillo and for $120 it was 10x better than this hotel. 
