<Author>The_Travelmeister
<Content>Beautiful scenery! Lousy Hotel! We just finished our stay at Bahia Salinas, and would really not consider staying again unless certain changes are made to the hotel and the staff. Bahia Salinas' location, on the southwest tip of Puerto Rico, is beautiful. It's a serene environment, with mangroves, and a nearby lighthouse and beach, as well as a nature preserve. Sunsets across the ocean are goregus, and the dark night skies are great for watching the stars (just bring lots of mosquito repellant or be prepared to be eaten alive). The hotel, billed as an upscale boutique hotel, leaves much to be desired. The rooms are small and rather spartan (bed, AC/TV, and not much else), some with small or nonexistent windows. What really got to me was the fact that in the morning we had no hot water. Argh! I'm paying $170 per night to have NO HOT WATER??? When we complained at the front desk, we were told that the hotel's water heater was solar powered. Oh.... so on cloudy days... no hot water? To top it off, the front desk's attitude was unapologetic, take it or leave it, as if to say, there's lot's of other people who want to stay here besides you, we're doing YOU a favor by letting you stay here. To be fair, the hotel pool is great and the landscaping tasteful. The restaurant food was overpriced, but good. So overall, the stay was wonderful, so long as we stayed OUTSIDE our room. The rooms and staffing attitude have to be brought up to par with the price! Next time we travel down to southwestern Puerto Rico we'll go enjoy the scenery, perhaps have dinner while enjoying the sunset, but head elsewhere to lodge. There are several places to stay along the coast. In la Parguera (Lajas) there are several cheap hotels. There's a parador hotel called Villa Parguera which is excellent (and half the price). A little further east in Guanica you can also find Copamarina Resort. It's more expensive than VIlla Parguera, but more peaceful and secluded. 
