<Content>Stayed an extra night We really enjoyed this hotel and even stayed an extra night. We were travelling with our two and a half year old and our room had two separate bedrooms. (A great option for kids)While the hotel is still under some construction, it is beautiful and we did not find the construction disturbing. (We are very early risers.) The shallow pool for kids was a great hit with our daughter, as was the caged birds near the restaurant and the hammock outside our door. We ate at the restaurant for two nights and two breakfasts on the meal plan as well as an additional lunch off the appetizer menu. We found one dinner to be much better than the other and the breakfast buffets to be very good. I would love to come back and see this hotel when it is completed. It is a lovely place to relax. Prices were between 80-$150 a night including the meal plan and there were only a few other guests. We felt this was a great deal. Please note that some of the information on the website is misleading since they are completely renovating the hotel and it was difficult to know what is new information and what was previously there. There is no playground for children as of May '06 and the spa and poolside restaurant were under construction. 
